  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause establishes that Bosch and Client operate independently, without shared control or responsibility for liabilities. However, it raises concerns regarding the lack of clarity on capital call mechanics, funding shortfalls, and potential audit restrictions.",
  "operative_text": "PARTIES: a) BOSCH TECHNOLOGIES, LLC ("

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines the subject matter of the joint venture, but lacks detail on financial mechanics and risk allocation.",
  "operative_text": "3. PRODUCT: \"Product \" BOSCH\" has acquired, developed and continues to develop, a business using proprietary \"Nano Printed Lights\", and associated other products (the \"Products\"). BOSCH calls this Nano Printed Lights product \"Printed LightSheets\" which is considered the \"Product Name\".",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks detail on financial mechanics and risk allocation, particularly regarding capital contributions, funding shortfalls, and liability.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 3"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

